	(105,1130,'0AUG418',104,1,'','Learning English through Movies',2863,'A','','H',2,1,'',1,'','N',0,'','',0,'','201',NULL,'5-6',0,'',NULL,20,0.27,0,75,2,'This course is designed to help students learn English by screening movies and analyzing some lines excerpted from the script. Students are required to bring a notebook to take notes when watching the movies. They are also encouraged to discuss and analyze the plots, themes, characters, and the lines of the movies screened. They are required to read the introductory excerpts prepared by the instructor before they watch the film. Six or five films are scheduled to be screened during the whole semester. We will spend three weeks reading part of the script, screening the film, and discussing the vocabulary, phrases, sentences, theme, plot, and cultural context of the film. Students are required to should prepare a notebook and note down English vocabularies, phrases, and sentences in the class. At the end of the semester students should turn in their notebooks. Notebook will take up 30 points. Also required is a ten minute short film adapted from the film we screen. Students should turn in the DVDs they produce in the second last week of the semester.',11,75,75,0,13,0,0,5,4),
