	(1833,1775,'ENU0168',104,1,'','English (I)',4066,'A','','H',3,56,'',1,'1','N',0,'','',0,'','304',NULL,'2-4',0,'',NULL,10,0.4,0,25,3,'The second semester of Freshman English is similar to the first semester of the course. Goals of the course remain the same: (1) to introduce students to readings on a wide variety of themes; (2) to teach students how to think critically about the issues addressed in the readings; (3) to discuss, in English, the issues addressed in the readings; (4) to help students become familiar with new vocabulary and culture points and discuss how they are used in the readings; and (5) to prepare students to be able to paraphrase passages from the readings and answer essay questions related to the readings. In the second semester there will be increased emphasis on having students discuss, in English, the readings for the course.',0,17,17,0,0,0,0,0,0),
