	(1921,1863,'ENU0038',104,1,'','Language Acquisition',4103,'','','H',3,56,'',0,'4','N',0,'1','',0,'','305',NULL,'6-8',0,'105104105104',NULL,20,0.4,3,50,3,'The major objective of this course is to inform students of second language acquisition research that can provide insights into second language teaching. However, as a preparation for the discussion of second language acquisition, we will begin with a brief introduction to some prominent features and theories of child first language development. The rest of the semester will then be devoted to discussion on the learning and teaching of a second language. The students are expected to become better able to analyze and evaluate the appropriateness of specific second language instructional practices based on second language acquisition theories and research.',0,29,29,0,5,0,0,0,1),
