	(3416,1390,'CLC8037',104,1,'','Seminar on Second Language Acquisition',5090,'','8','H',3,142,'',0,'','N',0,'1','',0,'','1003',NULL,'2-4',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,0,50,3,'The goal of this seminar is to first review the literature regarding the critical/sensitive period for the last 20 years and discuss the issues of UG and learning mechanisms in second language acquisition. The main focus for this first section will be the role of age and proficiency in second language acquisition; where relevant, first language acquisition and/or heritage language acquisition will also be examined for comparison. The second part of this course will discuss the issues of syntactic representation and learning of syntax in second language acquisition using structural/syntactic priming',0,4,4,0,0,0,0,0,0),
