	(3466,1404,'IWM0018',104,1,'','Human Resource Development',5124,'','','H',3,146,'',1,'1','N',0,'1','',0,'','104',NULL,'2-4',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,3,50,3,'COURSE DESCRIPTION & OBJECTIVES This course discusses theoretical foundations and practical aspects of human resource development (HRD) and its relation with organizational management. The purpose of this course is to help students understand history, definitions, implementation, and issues of HRD. Through lecture, group discussion, case study, and field interview, the course aims to develop students\' knowledge, abilities, and skills for conducting HRD in various types of organizations. More specifically, upon successful completion of this course, the student will be able to: 1.Understand the theoretical foundations of HRD 2.Familiar with the major processes of HRD 3.Gain insights about the practices of HRD in various businesses and organizations 4.Develop the skills in analyzing, designing, developing, implementing, and evaluating programs of HRD',0,19,19,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(3467,1405,'IWM0030',104,1,'','International Management',5125,'','','H',3,146,'',1,'1','N',0,'1','',0,'','104',NULL,'2-4',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,3,50,3,'Changes in the global business environment continue at an accelerated pace. The challenges for international management reflect this dynamism and the increasing unpredictability of global economic and political events. This course provides students with the current knowledge on how businesses can succeed in an international environment. Both the general effect of an international environment on organizations and the effect of operating in specific countries will be studied. Topics that will be particularly emphasized include: strategic factors related to `going global/international`, the effect of culture on various aspects of organizations, structures and processes that contribute to an organization`s international effectiveness, management practices in multinational companies, and the management of expatriate selection, development and assignments. This course is designed to prepare future employees and managers to work more effectively in a global workplace. It is taught using a combination of lectures, discussions, experiential exercises and short cases.',0,29,29,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(3468,1406,'IWM0040',104,1,'','Studies in Organizational Behavior',5126,'','','H',3,146,'',1,'1','N',0,'1','',0,'','104',NULL,'2-4',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,5,50,3,'The course will includes both theory and practical application of Organizational Behavior in organizations. The course is the study of how individuals and groups impact the behaviors within an organization. It is a field of systematic study that focuses on improving productivity and other areas of performance improvement. No previous study of Organizational Behavior is assumed.',0,28,28,0,0,0,0,0,0),
